&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain test plans, cases, and reports based on product requirements and industry standards (NVMe, PCIe, OCP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain sophisticated automated test scripts and frameworks using&amp;nbsp;Python&amp;nbsp;to drive regression suites and CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute functional, endurance, and stress tests on enterprise SSDs (U.2/U.3, EDSFF) to maximize coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and maintain enterprise server hardware (Dell, HPE, Supermicro), including BIOS/UEFI, RAID controllers, and networking setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze test results, log defects in JIRA, and drive root-cause analysis for complex system-level failures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage OS installations and configurations across Linux (RHEL, Ubuntu), Windows Server, and VMware vSphere/ESXi environments. Virtualization experience is a PLUS.&lt;/li&gt;
